and 35 are live.

1158
00:35:01,940 --> 00:35:04,920
We need to identify
the 15 unpowered buttons

1159
00:35:04,920 --> 00:35:07,870
and submit
the correct numbers in one try.

1160
00:35:07,870 --> 00:35:09,790
If you start randomly guessing,

1161
00:35:09,790 --> 00:35:12,300
I've got plenty
of ways to mess with you.

1162
00:35:12,300 --> 00:35:13,530
Just wait and see.

1163
00:35:14,360 --> 00:35:15,520
Who is that?

1164
00:35:15,520 --> 00:35:16,240
Who are you?

1165
00:35:16,240 --> 00:35:17,520
Who even are you?

1166
00:35:17,520 --> 00:35:20,040
Here's how to find
the unpowered buttons.

1167
00:35:20,230 --> 00:35:24,240
(Method to Find Unpowered Buttons)
One player holds the electrified rod.

1168
00:35:24,240 --> 00:35:26,540
Pick any two numbers.

1169
00:35:26,540 --> 00:35:29,240
If either button is live,

1170
00:35:29,240 --> 00:35:30,740
the player gets shocked.

1171
00:35:30,740 --> 00:35:33,020
If both buttons are unpowered,

1172
00:35:33,020 --> 00:35:34,780
the player won't get shocked.

1173
00:35:34,820 --> 00:35:36,020
(Fibonacci sequence, perfect squares)

1174
00:35:36,020 --> 00:35:38,980
(50 buttons,
15 unpowered, probability theory)

1175
00:35:39,280 --> 00:35:39,760
We...

1176
00:35:39,820 --> 00:35:40,820
(Got an idea?)

1177
00:35:42,160 --> 00:35:44,600
Let's do hand-in-hand-out
to see who goes first.

1178
00:35:49,880 --> 00:35:51,560
I'll do it.

1179
00:35:52,360 --> 00:35:53,000
You go.

1180
00:35:53,960 --> 00:35:54,400
I'll go.

1181
00:35:54,400 --> 00:35:54,600
Fine.

1182
00:35:54,600 --> 00:35:55,280
Wait, hold on.

1183
00:35:55,280 --> 00:35:56,000
(Totally not panicking)
Let's think this through.

1184
00:35:56,000 --> 00:35:56,840
How are we supposed to play this?

1185
00:35:56,840 --> 00:35:57,800
We can't just brute-force it.

1186
00:35:57,800 --> 00:35:58,880
This is basically a math problem.

1187
00:35:58,880 --> 00:35:59,800
Let's test one and two first.

1188
00:35:59,800 --> 00:36:01,880
If we get shocked,
then try one and three.

1189
00:36:01,880 --> 00:36:04,840
Eventually, we'll find a pair
with no electricity.

1190
00:36:05,000 --> 00:36:06,440
But what if button one is always live?

1191
00:36:08,160 --> 00:36:08,840
How about this?

1192
00:36:08,840 --> 00:36:09,640
Let's test them

1193
00:36:09,640 --> 00:36:10,720
in a pattern.

1194
00:36:12,040 --> 00:36:12,560
This column

1195
00:36:12,560 --> 00:36:14,720
against that column.

1196
00:36:14,720 --> 00:36:15,360
(Test Strategy)
We pair

1197
00:36:15,360 --> 00:36:16,280
(Pair outer rows and move inward.)
opposite numbers

1198
00:36:16,280 --> 00:36:16,880
and work inward one by one.

1199
00:36:16,880 --> 00:36:18,120
If we don't

1200
00:36:18,440 --> 00:36:19,240
find any matches,

1201
00:36:19,240 --> 00:36:22,400
then we eliminate that row
and start testing within the next one.

1202
00:36:23,040 --> 00:36:23,520
Okay.

1203
00:36:23,520 --> 00:36:24,880
Maybe there's some kind of symmetry,

1204
00:36:24,880 --> 00:36:25,720
and we'll hit
two unpowered ones together.

1205
00:36:25,720 --> 00:36:26,320
Right.

1206
00:36:26,320 --> 00:36:28,120
So, one and ten. Two and nine.

1207
00:36:28,120 --> 00:36:28,520
That works.

1208
00:36:29,400 --> 00:36:30,160
Zhou.

1209
00:36:34,320 --> 00:36:36,280
You guys casually
volunteered someone to go up there.

1210
00:36:36,280 --> 00:36:36,960
Zhou, you go first.

1211
00:36:36,960 --> 00:36:37,440
You go first.

1212
00:36:37,440 --> 00:36:38,800
We feel bad about it,

1213
00:36:38,800 --> 00:36:40,000
