voted correctly receive a Golden Key.

1413
00:42:23,360 --> 00:42:24,440
(Killer, Player)
If the killer

1414
00:42:24,440 --> 00:42:26,080
receives fewer votes
than another suspect,

1415
00:42:26,080 --> 00:42:27,280
then the killer player

1416
00:42:27,280 --> 00:42:29,000
gets the Golden Key instead.

1417
00:42:32,680 --> 00:42:33,720
Why are you laughing?

1418
00:42:33,720 --> 00:42:34,960
Your smile today is kinda creepy.

1419
00:42:35,240 --> 00:42:36,680
I'm getting a Golden Key today.

1420
00:42:37,240 --> 00:42:39,000
(Determined to win)
Nobody's stopping me.

1421
00:42:39,000 --> 00:42:40,960
(Game Rules: Suspects, NPCs, Killer)
After each dungeon,

1422
00:42:40,960 --> 00:42:43,080
players return to the game lobby

1423
00:42:43,080 --> 00:42:44,400
for Golden Key tallying.

1424
00:42:44,400 --> 00:42:45,320
(Player)

1425
00:42:45,320 --> 00:42:46,400
Attention.

1426
00:42:46,400 --> 00:42:47,600
Golden Keys

1427
00:42:47,600 --> 00:42:49,600
aren't just symbols of victory.

1428
00:42:49,600 --> 00:42:51,320
They can also
be exchanged for Skill Cards.

1429
00:42:51,320 --> 00:42:52,260
(Skill Cards)

1430
00:42:53,080 --> 00:42:54,240
I love Skill Cards.

1431
00:42:54,240 --> 00:42:55,120
They're super useful.

1432
00:42:55,120 --> 00:42:57,080
(Time Extension Card,
Restore Card, Lights Out Card)

1433
00:42:57,080 --> 00:42:57,720
First-time players entering a dungeon

1434
00:42:57,720 --> 00:42:59,440
(Soothing Card, Copy Card, Rewind Card)
receive one free Skill Card.

1435
00:42:59,800 --> 00:43:01,600
Please choose your Skill Card

1436
00:43:01,600 --> 00:43:03,120
and set a trigger gesture.

1437
00:43:04,680 --> 00:43:06,840
The Time Extension Card can
extend certain timed segments.

1438
00:43:06,840 --> 00:43:09,040
Like that time we failed to pull you up,

1439
00:43:09,040 --> 00:43:10,720
(See The Truth Season 3,
Episode 2 (Part 1))

1440
00:43:10,720 --> 00:43:11,920
I activated a skill,
and the door stopped.

1441
00:43:12,840 --> 00:43:15,000
We were literally seconds away.

1442
00:43:15,000 --> 00:43:15,920
Skill Card Two.

1443
00:43:15,980 --> 00:43:17,080
(Restore Card)

1444
00:43:17,080 --> 00:43:17,480
Restore...

1445
00:43:17,480 --> 00:43:18,560
Restore a clue.

1446
00:43:19,600 --> 00:43:20,960
Restore the clue

1447
00:43:20,960 --> 00:43:22,520
to replay how the crime happened.

1448
00:43:23,240 --> 00:43:24,360
At that point, you might as well

1449
00:43:24,360 --> 00:43:25,280
just ask the killer directly.

1450
00:43:25,280 --> 00:43:25,800
I want to restore it.

1451
00:43:25,800 --> 00:43:26,640
Restore the crime scene.

1452
00:43:26,640 --> 00:43:27,920
Then the killer walks in like,

1453
00:43:27,920 --> 00:43:28,920
(First this, then that)
"Here's how I did it".

1454
00:43:28,980 --> 00:43:31,100
(Straight to the ending)

1455
00:43:31,760 --> 00:43:32,730
(Lights Out Card)
Skill Card Three.

1456
00:43:32,800 --> 00:43:33,680
Turn off the lights once.

1457
00:43:33,680 --> 00:43:35,360
What kind of useless card is that?

1458
00:43:35,360 --> 00:43:37,680
That sounds like a killer's card.

1459
00:43:38,940 --> 00:43:40,020
(Copy Card:
Copy any player's Skill Card)

1460
00:43:40,040 --> 00:43:40,560
Copy Card.

1461
00:43:41,160 --> 00:43:41,760
That one's strong.

1462
00:43:41,780 --> 00:43:42,600
(Unstoppable)

1463
00:43:42,600 --> 00:43:43,240
This one's the best.

1464
00:43:43,880 --> 00:43:44,600
This is good.

1465
00:43:44,880 --> 00:43:46,040
It's like the Star Absorption Technique.

1466
00:43:46,040 --> 00:43:46,800
It copies.

1467
00:43:46,800 --> 00:43:48,160
It doesn't steal.

1468
00:43:48,220 --> 00:43:49,240
(Very precise wording)

1469
00:43:49,240 --> 00:43:49,800
Exactly.

1470
00:43:50,180 --> 00:43:51,360
(Soothing Card: Calm an NPC's emotions)

1471
00:43:51,360 --> 00:43:52,360
Soothing Card.

1472
00:43:52,360 --> 00:43:53,520
Like if you run

1473
00:43:53,520 --> 00:43:54,960
into a terrifying scene

1474
00:43:54,960 --> 00:43:56,160
or an NPC loses it,

1475
00:43:56,160 --> 00:43:57,000
you calm them down.

1476
00:43:57,000 --> 00:43:58,160
Yeah. You told me to stay calm.

1477
00:43:58,480 --> 00:43:59,120
Perfect for you guys.

1478
00:44:00,180 --> 00:44:01,380
(Interested)

1479
00:44:01,400 --> 00:44:02,160
Can we buy?

1480
00:44:02,160 --> 00:44:03,320
I wanna bulk order these.

1481
00:44:03,320 --> 00:44:04,260
(I want a lot of it)

1482
00:44:04,740 --> 00:44:06,080
(Rewind Card:
Makes an NPC repeat their last line)

1483
00:44:06,080 --> 00:44:07,240
Like if we missed something,

1484
00:44:07,240 --> 00:44:08,160
we can hear it again.

1485
00:44:08,160 --> 00:44:09,640
That means NPCs

1486
00:44:09,640 --> 00:44:11,320
will play a huge role this season.

1487
00:44:12,240 --> 00:44:12,640
Definitely.

1488
00:44:13,280 --> 00:44:15,200
(Skill Cards)
Everyone can pick one card.

1489
00:44:15,200 --> 00:44:16,400
Here's the real question.

1490
00:44:16,400 --> 00:44:18,280
Are we choosing

1491
00:44:18,280 --> 00:44:18,920
these cards

1492
00:44:18,920 --> 00:44:20,880
as teammates,

1493
00:44:20,880 --> 00:44:22,720
or as opponents?

1494
00:44:23,960 --> 00:44:26,560
The show just started filming,
so for now, we're teammates.

1495
00:44:26,560 --> 00:44:27,080
Sound good?

1496
00:44:28,000 --> 00:44:30,400
Then I'm taking the Copy Card first.

1497
00:44:30,660 --> 00:44:32,340
(Wait, that's allowed?)

1498
00:44:32,560 --> 00:44:33,800
You're taking Copy Card?

1499
00:44:33,800 --> 00:44:34,200
You?

1500
00:44:34,200 --> 00:44:34,780
(Strikes a pose)

1501
00:44:36,360 --> 00:44:37,560
Do you want the Copy Card?

1502
00:44:39,320 --> 00:44:40,520
Doesn't seem that impressive.

1503
00:44:40,520 --> 00:44:41,680
Then I'll take Soothing Card,
and you take Copy Card.

1504
00:44:41,680 --> 00:44:42,960
It's fine.

1505
00:44:42,960 --> 00:44:43,760
(You take Copy Card)

1506
00:44:43,760 --> 00:44:44,880
Alright then, I'll take Copy Card.

1507
00:44:45,100 --> 00:44:46,140
(Gladly)

1508
00:44:46,520 --> 00:44:46,960
Like this.

1509
00:44:46,960 --> 00:44:47,900
(Set Skill Card trigger gesture)

1510
00:44:48,080 --> 00:44:49,120
No matter what card I use,
I'm doing this.

1511
00:44:49,120 --> 00:44:49,960
Six Meridians Sword.

1512
00:44:49,960 --> 00:44:51,420
(Copy Card:
Copy any player's Skill Card)

1513
00:44:51,760 --> 00:44:53,520
Okay, I'm using the Soothing Card.

1514
00:44:53,740 --> 00:44:54,680
(Soothing Card: Calm an NPC's emotions)

1515
00:44:54,680 --> 00:44:55,680
Do you guys wanna pick first?

1516
00:44:55,740 --> 00:44:56,760
(Being polite)

1517
00:44:56,760 --> 00:44:57,040
Ning.

1518
00:44:57,040 --> 00:44:57,840
Extend the time.

1519
00:44:57,840 --> 00:44:59,200
I'll use the Time Extension Card.

1520
00:44:59,200 --> 00:44:59,680
(Time Extension Card:
Extend timed segments)

1521
00:44:59,680 --> 00:45:00,400
Okay.

1522
00:45:00,400 --> 00:45:02,040
Honestly,
I don't think Rewind is that useful.

1523
00:45:02,040 --> 00:45:03,760
(Ning chose Time Extension Card)
Maybe it is.

1524
00:45:03,760 --> 00:45:04,880
(Jin chose Soothing Card)
If NPCs really matter

1525
00:45:04,880 --> 00:45:05,960
(Ding chose Copy Card)
that much this season,

1526
00:45:05,960 --> 00:45:07,280
there's probably gonna
be tons of information.

1527
00:45:07,280 --> 00:45:08,360
Then let's skip Lights Out.

1528
00:45:08,360 --> 00:45:09,560
That card feels too physical.

1529
00:45:09,560 --> 00:45:10,240
Skip it.

1530
00:45:10,240 --> 00:45:10,840
I'll take Rewind then.

1531
00:45:10,840 --> 00:45:11,400
(He chose Rewind Card)
Rewind Card.

1532
00:45:11,400 --> 00:45:12,720
(Ke chose Restore Card)
Then I'll take Restore Card.

1533
00:45:12,720 --> 00:45:13,120
Okay.

1534
00:45:13,240 --> 00:45:14,960
I want to use Rewind Card.

1535
00:45:14,960 --> 00:45:15,920
(Rewind Card:
Makes an NPC repeat their last line)

1536
00:45:15,920 --> 00:45:16,440
Okay.

1537
00:45:16,440 --> 00:45:17,200
Nice.

1538
00:45:18,600 --> 00:45:19,760
I want to use the Restore Card.

1539
00:45:20,160 --> 00:45:20,960
Nice.

1540
00:45:20,960 --> 00:45:21,840
This one.

1541
00:45:22,000 --> 00:45:23,500
I want to use the Restore Card.

1542
00:45:23,500 --> 00:45:24,280
